# Meridian Exercise: Bayesian MMM with Google's Package

## What You'll Build

A full Bayesian Marketing Mix Model using [Google Meridian](https://developers.google.com/meridian/docs) — the same framework Google uses internally and shares with advertisers. By the end you will have:

- Estimated ROI for 4 media channels with credible intervals
- Response curves showing where each channel saturates
- A budget reallocation recommendation
- Hands-on experience tuning Bayesian priors

**Estimated time:** 2–4 hours (including model fitting, which takes ~10–20 min on CPU)

---

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.11, 3.12, or 3.13
- Basic Python and pandas familiarity
- Jupyter installed (`pip install jupyter`)
- ~4 GB RAM free during model fitting

> **macOS note:** Meridian uses TensorFlow, which does not support GPU on macOS. The model will run on CPU. This is fine for the exercise dataset (104 weeks) but will be slower on larger real datasets.

