## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| `ImportError: No module named 'meridian'` | You're outside the venv. Run `source venv/bin/activate` |
| `ModuleNotFoundError: tensorflow` | Run `pip install tensorflow` inside the venv |
| Model fitting hangs >30 min | Reduce `num_samples=200` in the notebook's fit call |
| R-hat > 1.1 warnings | Try `num_warmup=500` (more warmup); usually fixes convergence |
| Memory error during fit | Close other apps; or reduce to `num_chains=2` |

